Spanish reporter Miguel Rico has issued a short but eye-catching piece of transfer news on Wednesday. Writing in Mundo Deportivo, it’s claimed Barcelona were interested in signing Lucas Moura from Tottenham this summer. Barcelona allegedly considered moving for Moura as an alternative to Neymar. As we now know after the close of the European transfer window yesterday, Neymar ended up staying at PSG.   👊 A pivotal moment in last year’s #UCL group stage! 🔥⚡️ #COYS #THFC A post shared by  Tottenham Hotspur (@spursofficial) on Aug 29, 2019 at 5:45am PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js So why didn’t Barcelona land Moura? According to Mundo Deportivo, Tottenham were asking for more than 50 million euros for the attacking midfielder. Moura, 27, is under contract with Spurs until 2022. Tottenham paid around £25 million to buy Moura from PSG back in January 2018. Reading between the lines, however, the messages seems to be that Spurs would have sold Moura had Barcelona paid up. It’s been a strange start to the season for Tottenham. After losing last year’s Champions League final, Mauricio Pochettino’s men opened with a come-from-behind win against Aston Villa. Spurs then drew 2-2 at Man City, with Moura coming off the bench to head home his first of the season.   🔊 Sound ON and listen to @lucasmoura7’s scream! 💙 #COYS #THFC A post shared by  Tottenham Hotspur (@spursofficial) on Aug 19, 2019 at 3:12am PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js Newcastle stunned Tottenham with a 1-0 away win in north London. Last weekend, Tottenham blew a 2-goal lead in the north London derby in a 2-2 draw at Arsenal. Tottenham are ninth in the Premier League with 5 points from 4 games. Also see: Arsenal, Chelsea & Tottenham: 25-man Premier League squads confirmed. Liverpool’s Virgil van Dijk registered the fastest sprint in 2018/19 Champions League. Source: Great Goals Alderweireld shows United what they are missing, clinical Tottenham and other things we learnt from Monday night clash. Tottenham pile mo